[list][item]To join in, make sure you have your safety goggles ((safety goggles)) handy! You can get these from the starter pack ((Beatrix's Booming Brawl Box)), via [[Daily Chores]] monthly rewards (14 days), or by trading with other players (they are mailable). [/item][item]Make sure the ((safety goggles)) are in your inventory and not your storehouse or you won't be able to access the game.[/item][item]Each hour, you get 5 attempts to fire off bottle rockets, and you can bank up to 25 attempts.[/item][item]Select a shield to defend yourself, and choose your attacks wisely! Each attack will target 5-10 players at random.[/item][item]You need ((Bottle Rocket)) and some of whichever shield you choose to defend with in your inventory.[/item][item]If you get hit, you'll lose HP. You recover 100 every hour, but if you reach 0, you'll have to wait until the top of the next hour to fire more bottle rockets.[/item][item]There isn't a log of shots fired/taken and is unlikely to be implemented due to the logging overhead.[/item][item]Each successful hit will earn you an event token ((event token)). Keep an eye on [updates] for news about the event shop, coming soon.[/item][item]If you're struggling to access the BRB mini-game page, try clicking the refresh button on the home page.[/item][/list]

[color=transparent][d=Shield & Bottle Rocket type mechanics][list][item]Wooden shields ((wooden shield)) are strong against Strike Shot (brown), green shields ((green shield)) are strong against Blast Shot (green), and red shields ((red shield)) are strong against Inferno Shot (red). Try to guess what other players might be using![/item][/list][/d][/color]